cs.CC, cs.DS, cs.DM, cs.GT, cs.LO

This paper deals with the complexity of approximation on satisfiable instances for graph homomorphism problems, which is a topic in computational complexity theory. Therefore, cs.CC (Computational Complexity) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also involves the study of graph theory and algebraic topology, which suggests that it could also belong to cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) and cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory). Additionally, the paper involves the study of promise constraint satisfaction problems, which could place it in cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics) or cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science).
